Gombe State Police Command in conjunction with hunters in the state  have shot and killed a kidnapper whose identity was yet to be ascertained. His accomplice, one Babangida Musa who was arrested and paraded, confessed to the crime. The CPS said yesterday, that : “Armed bandits/kidnappers invaded Yelwa village via Kashere, Pindiga Division, Akko LGA of Gombe State and entered the house of one Mallam Kawu Amada, 50 years and Musa Rufayi, 30 years; all of same address and thereby inflicted bodily injuries on Mallam Kawu Amada and kidnapped Musa Rufayi alongside his Bajaj  motorcycle to unknown destination”. “Along the way, Musa Rufayi escaped unhurt”. “Based on distress call from O/C Kashere, a combined team of police patrol, SARS operatives and hunters led by DPO,  Pindiga blocked Badara routes  via Kashere Pindiga Division”. “On sighting the policemen, the hoodlums exchanged fire with the policemen and as a result, one of the kidnappers was gunned down and one Babangida Musa who is also one of the kidnappers was arrested while others fled with gunshot injuries”.